and make a decision.

186
00:12:55,141 --> 00:12:59,278
Two armed intruders hold a judge
against his will in his home.

187
00:12:59,311 --> 00:13:01,280
Robbery is not the motive.

188
00:13:01,313 --> 00:13:04,450
With all of your years of
experience, your vast

189
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:11,557
legal knowledge, tell me,
what is your conclusion?

190
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:13,492
Do I know you two?

191
00:13:13,526 --> 00:13:16,128
We're not important.

192
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:18,297
I'm a family court judge.

193
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:19,565
Not criminal.

194
00:13:19,598 --> 00:13:20,566
We're not criminals.

195
00:13:20,599 --> 00:13:22,434
Neither one of us has
ever committed a crime.

196
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:24,103
Or served a day in jail.

197
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,237
Okay.

198
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:28,007
I didn't mean anything by it.

199
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,342
You're both very young.

200
00:13:30,376 --> 00:13:32,311
You don't wanna
throw your lives away.

201
00:13:32,344 --> 00:13:34,146
You're not worried
about our lives.

202
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,482
You're gonna say whatever you
have to say to get out of this.

203
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:38,417
To get back to your
Saturday golf outings,

204
00:13:38,450 --> 00:13:40,319
and your Sunday family dinners.

205
00:13:40,352 --> 00:13:42,288
Having a good time, enjoying
life while you sit in your

206
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:45,558
courtroom acting like God.

207
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:53,599
The reckless decisions
you make destroy lives.

208
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:58,404
I fully understand the
impact that my rulings

209
00:13:58,437 --> 00:14:00,573
have on people's lives.

210
00:14:00,606 --> 00:14:06,212
That is not something
that I take lightly.

211
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:14,253
Uh-huh.

212
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:25,364
I stand by every
decision I've ever made.

213
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:28,234
Well so do I.

214
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:29,335
John!

215
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:31,470
[blood pours out]

216
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:33,305
Holy shit.

217
00:14:33,339 --> 00:14:41,347
[judge gags and struggles]

218
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:45,351
Oh my God.

219
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:47,486
Did you get that?

220
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:49,488
Yeah.

221
