[knife cuts into the
air and Judy's body]

557
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:21,833
Fuck!

558
00:33:21,866 --> 00:33:28,106
[wiping sound and
birds chirping]

559
00:33:28,139 --> 00:33:30,408
Kenny, what are you doing?

560
00:33:30,441 --> 00:33:38,449
[heavy breathing]

561
00:33:42,387 --> 00:33:45,823
So what do you think?

562
00:33:45,857 --> 00:33:50,228
[street noise
and birds chirping]

563
00:33:50,261 --> 00:33:58,269
[diner music and chatter]

564
00:34:00,304 --> 00:34:05,710
[diner music and chatter]

565
00:34:05,743 --> 00:34:07,245
Here you go.

566
00:34:07,278 --> 00:34:09,313
Thank you.

567
00:34:09,347 --> 00:34:14,619
Enjoy.

568
00:34:14,652 --> 00:34:16,487
I need to get some coffee.

569
00:34:16,521 --> 00:34:19,524
So do I.

570
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:21,459
You hungry?

571
00:34:21,492 --> 00:34:22,627
Not really.

572
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,496
[phone ringing]

573
00:34:25,530 --> 00:34:26,664
Is that you?

574
00:34:26,697 --> 00:34:27,732
Yeah.

575
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:29,467
[phone ringing]

576
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:30,601
It's Andrea.

577
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:32,203
Andrea?

578
00:34:32,236 --> 00:34:33,805
Yeah, it's her.

579
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:34,372
[phone ringing]

580
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:35,506
It's gotta be about dad.

581
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:36,607
Well answer it.

582
00:34:36,641 --> 00:34:38,176
I don't know what to say.

583
00:34:38,209 --> 00:34:38,876
Just talk to her.

584
00:34:38,910 --> 00:34:40,611
You've stayed in touch with her.

585
00:34:40,645 --> 00:34:42,380
Let's just see if she
leaves a voicemail.

586
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:43,614
[phone ringing]

587
00:34:43,648 --> 00:34:49,187
Hey, how's everything going?

588
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:50,221
[Andrea on voicemail] Hi, Kenny.

589
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:53,291
It's your big sister.

590
00:34:53,324 --> 00:34:55,927
I'm not sure why I'm calling.

591
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:58,596
I know you and John
want to be left alone,

592
00:34:58,629 --> 00:35:03,701
but for what it's worth,
I saw dad last night.

593
00:35:03,734 --> 00:35:10,308
I actually just left their
house and he's getting worse.

594
00:35:10,341 --> 00:35:15,246
I thought you should know.

595
00:35:15,279 --> 00:35:18,516
[birds chirping]

596
00:35:18,549 --> 00:35:26,557
[movement in the car]

597
00:35:28,392 --> 00:35:34,765
[movement in the car]

598
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:36,701
[heavy sigh]

599
00:35:36,734 --> 00:35:39,904
Come on, Kenny.

600
00:35:39,937 --> 00:35:42,206
Jesus Christ.

601
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:45,409
[birds chirping]

602
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:47,979
Kenny!

603
00:35:48,012 --> 00:35:50,381
I'm over here!

604
00:35:50,414 --> 00:35:52,450
Well where's here?!

605
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:55,419
Down by the stream!

606
00:35:55,453 --> 00:35:58,389
What Cupful stream?

607
00:35:58,422 --> 00:36:04,929
[birds chirping and footsteps]

608
00:36:04,962 --> 00:36:06,864
How are you making out?

609
00:36:06,898 --> 00:36:12,603
Good.

610
00:36:12,637 --> 00:36:15,339
Let me see what you got.

611
00:36:15,373 --> 00:36:18,943
[sounds of nature]

612
00:36:18,976 --> 00:36:23,848
[camera makes a beeping
sound with each picture]

613
00:36:23,881 --> 00:36:25,716
These look really great, bro.

614
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:30,655
Thanks.

615
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:34,892
Listen, I know this is kinda
how you process things,

616
00:36:34,926 --> 00:36:37,695
but we really gotta get moving.

617
00:36:37,728 --> 00:36:41,999
Yeah, just give me
a few more minutes.

618
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:47,405
[sounds of nature]

619
00:36:47,438 --> 00:36:55,513
[car sounds]

620
00:36:55,546 --> 00:37:00,051
[dogs barking, cars honking]

621
00:37:00,084 --> 00:37:08,292
[sounds of nature]

622
00:37:10,394 --> 00:37:18,402
[sounds of nature]

623
00:37:20,438 --> 00:37:26,777
[sounds of nature]

624
00:37:26,811 --> 00:37:28,713
So what do you wanna do?

625
00:37:28,746 --> 00:37:33,417
Just sit here and wait.

626
00:37:33,451 --> 00:37:37,655
Let her go inside,
we'll give it a little time.

627
00:37:37,688 --> 00:37:45,696
[outside noise]

628
00:37:47,465 --> 00:37:48,399
[car starts]

629
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:49,433
Shit.

630
00:37:49,467 --> 00:37:50,835
Try to block her.

631
00:37:50,868 --> 00:37:52,069
It's too risky.

632
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:52,637
It's daylight.

633
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,538
Somebody might see us.

634
00:37:54,572 --> 00:37:57,108
So you wanna leave?

635
00:37:57,141 --> 00:38:01,812
No, let's just follow
her and see what happens.

636
00:38:01,846 --> 00:38:09,854
[car noise]

637
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:19,964
[car noise]

638
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:34,578
[kids playing]

639
00:38:36,414 --> 00:38:44,522
[kids playing]

640
00:38:44,555 --> 00:38:47,458
What do you think?

641
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:50,428
Think she's gonna
remove the kids?

642
00:38:50,461 --> 00:38:52,897
I don't think so.

643
00:38:52,930 --> 00:38:55,399
The kids look too happy.

644
00:38:55,433 --> 00:38:58,969
It's a foster home.

645
00:38:59,003 --> 00:39:02,573
It's their escape from insanity.

646
00:39:02,606 --> 00:39:06,143
Until they decide to send
them back to their parents,

647
00:39:06,177 --> 00:39:14,385
the same people that put
them here to begin with.

648
00:39:21,058 --> 00:39:24,962
Is there anyone around?

649
00:39:24,995 --> 00:39:26,163
I don't see anyone.

650
00:39:26,197 --> 00:39:27,932
Well, keep an eye out.

651
00:39:27,965 --> 00:39:29,533
You wanna do this now?

652
00:39:29,567 --> 00:39:31,502
This might be the
best chance we have.

653
00:39:31,535 --> 00:39:32,670
John, let's think about this.

654
00:39:32,703 --> 00:39:34,438
She probably has
another appointment today.

655
00:39:34,472 --> 00:39:37,575
Or she's expected
back at her office.

656
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:39,510
Wait, if she doesn't
show up, the police are

657
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:41,145
gonna look for her.

658
00:39:41,178 --> 00:39:43,481
Let's do it at her house
tonight, It'll buy us more time.

659
00:39:43,514 --> 00:39:49,487
I'm not doing this
in front of her kids.

660
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:54,091
[car opens and closes]

661
00:39:54,125 --> 00:39:56,794
[Woman screams]
Jesus.

662
00:39:56,827 --> 00:39:59,697
Did anybody fucking see him?

663
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:00,131
Come on!

664
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:01,599
Help me!

665
00:40:01,632 --> 00:40:09,640
[car noise]

666
00:40:11,642 --> 00:40:17,214
[car noise]

667
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:25,456
[car noise]

668
00:40:27,291 --> 00:40:32,863
[car noise]

669
00:40:32,897 --> 00:40:40,905
[car noise]

670
00:40:42,940 --> 00:40:48,512
[car noise]

671
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:56,554
[car noise]

672
00:40:58,589 --> 00:41:04,195
[car noise]

673
00:41:04,228 --> 00:41:08,299
[puts car in park]

674
00:41:08,332 --> 00:41:16,540
[sounds of nature]

675
00:41:18,242 --> 00:41:23,647
[sounds of nature]

676
00:41:23,681 --> 00:41:25,683
Are you okay?

677
00:41:25,716 --> 00:41:26,884
Yeah.

678
00:41:26,917 --> 00:41:29,253
[sounds of nature]

679
00:41:29,286 --> 00:41:32,289
I'm gonna carry her in.

680
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:38,128
[sounds of nature]

681
00:41:38,162 --> 00:41:43,067
[woman screams]

682
00:41:43,100 --> 00:41:45,269
Somebody!
Help me!

683
00:41:45,302 --> 00:41:46,270
I thought you tied her up!

684
00:41:46,303 --> 00:41:47,071
I did!

685
00:41:47,104 --> 00:41:49,807
She got out of it!

686
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:52,076
[footsteps and heavy breathing]

687
00:41:52,109 --> 00:41:56,580
[woman screams]

688
00:41:56,614 --> 00:41:57,748
Leave me alone!

689
00:41:57,781 --> 00:42:00,584
No!

690
00:42:00,618 --> 00:42:03,954
[struggles and heavy breathing]

691
00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:07,258
Help me get her
inside the fuckin' house.

692
00:42:07,291 --> 00:42:09,627
[sounds of nature]
Come on!

693
00:42:09,660 --> 00:42:17,668
[footsteps]

694
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:27,711
[footsteps]

695
00:42:28,245 --> 00:42:30,714
[crickets chirping]

696
00:42:30,748 --> 00:42:33,150
Please.

697
00:42:33,183 --> 00:42:36,754
I have two little
boys, I'm all they have.

698
00:42:36,787 --> 00:42:38,822
I told you to be quiet!

699
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:46,864
[woman sobs]

700
00:42:49,366 --> 00:42:57,374
[woman sobs]

701
00:42:59,910 --> 00:43:07,918
[woman sobs]

702
00:43:10,321 --> 00:43:18,329
[footsteps around the house]

703
00:43:25,202 --> 00:43:28,439
This house once
brought happiness.

704
00:43:28,472 --> 00:43:36,680
It brought safety and security
when everything was crazy.

705
00:43:37,815 --> 00:43:40,317
There was an older
couple that owned this house.

706
00:43:40,351 --> 00:43:42,453
They couldn't have
children of their own

707
00:43:42,486 --> 00:43:45,255
so they filled it
with foster kids.

708
00:43:45,289 --> 00:43:47,124
Do you remember them?

709
00:43:47,157 --> 00:43:49,760
Fred and Helen Decker.

710
00:43:49,793 --> 00:43:50,961
That's right.

711
00:43:50,995 --> 00:43:52,930
I'm surprised you
remember their names.

712
00:43:52,963 --> 00:43:56,734
I figured you'd know them
by some state-assigned code.

713
00:43:56,767 --> 00:43:58,235
They were good people.

714
00:43:58,268 --> 00:44:00,304
They were great people.

715
00:44:00,337 --> 00:44:03,841
Fred passed away
about eight years ago.

716
00:44:03,874 --> 00:44:05,376
I know he did.

717
00:44:05,409 --> 00:44:08,946
And I know Helen lost this
place about five years ago.

718
00:44:08,979 --> 00:44:12,416
She did everything she
could to try to keep it.

719
00:44:12,449 --> 00:44:17,121
But it was just too much
for her after losing Fred.

720
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:19,189
So after helping others
for most of her life,

721
00:44:19,223 --> 00:44:20,324
she now gets to spend
what little time she has

722
00:44:20,357 --> 00:44:24,328
left in a state-run
nursing home.

723
00:44:24,361 --> 00:44:28,365
Where she can be taken
care of for a change.

724
00:44:28,399 --> 00:44:34,338
She's just another number.

725
00:44:34,371 --> 00:44:36,740
We're all just numbers, right?

726
00:44:36,774 --> 00:44:41,311
How we live, how we die,
how much money we make.

727
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:44,381
And then decisions are
made that affect peoples' lives

728
00:44:44,415 --> 00:44:47,351
based on statistics.

729
00:44:47,384 --> 00:44:49,953
I never looked at the
two of you that way.

730
00:44:49,987 --> 00:44:52,289
What did you say?

731
00:44:52,322 --> 00:44:54,324
I remember you.

732
00:44:54,358 --> 00:44:58,362
John and Kenneth Stiles,
and your sister Andrea.

733
00:44:58,395 --> 00:45:00,364
Obviously, you're
both a lot older now

734
00:45:00,397 --> 00:45:03,300
but I recognized you right away.

735
00:45:03,333 --> 00:45:05,302
And the way the two of
you interact with each other,

736
00:45:05,335 --> 00:45:08,172
it hasn't changed.

737
00:45:08,205 --> 00:45:10,407
I don't know why
you're doing this to me.

738
00:45:10,441 --> 00:45:11,508
You don't?

739
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,211
I don't.

740
00:45:14,244 --> 00:45:17,314
I did everything I could to
protect the three of you.

741
00:45:17,347 --> 00:45:19,983
I had you removed from an
abusive home and placed

742
00:45:20,017 --> 00:45:22,386
in a safe environment
here with the Deckers.

743
00:45:22,419 --> 00:45:24,088
I tried to help you.

744
00:45:24,121 --> 00:45:25,956
But you sent us
back to our parents.

745
00:45:25,989 --> 00:45:28,058
It's always in the best interest
of the children to be with

746
00:45:28,092 --> 00:45:29,426
their biological parents.

747
00:45:29,460 --> 00:45:31,428
Even if there's abuse?

748
00:45:31,462 --> 00:45:32,396
Of course not.

749
00:45:32,429 --> 00:45:33,630
When there's abuse,
we remove the children.

750
00:45:33,664 --> 00:45:36,533
Then the parents are given a
case plan and if they follow it,

751
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:39,169
then they'll regain custody.

752
00:45:39,203 --> 00:45:42,473
And I'm assuming my parents
followed it to perfection.

753
00:45:42,506 --> 00:45:44,875
They did everything
they were required to do.

754
00:45:44,908 --> 00:45:46,510
I had to tell the judge that.

755
00:45:46,543 --> 00:45:49,346
And in his divine wisdom
he sent us back to them.

756
00:45:49,379 --> 00:45:52,216
It's not our goal to
break up families.

757
00:45:52,249 --> 00:45:55,419
Our first priority is
to protect the children.

758
00:45:55,452 --> 00:45:56,687
Like in our case.

759
00:45:56,720 --> 00:46:00,858
Your parents demonstrated that
they had a safe and stable home.

760
00:46:00,891 --> 00:46:02,226
A safe, stable home?

761
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:04,461
Do you have any idea how
horrific the abuse was when

762
00:46:04,495 --> 00:46:05,629
you sent us back to them?

763
00:46:05,662 --> 00:46:08,432
When I came to your house
and everything seemed okay.

764
00:46:08,465 --> 00:46:09,900
Oh, bullshit!

765
00:46:09,933 --> 00:46:11,034
You think checking
up on us every

766
00:46:11,068 --> 00:46:12,469
here and there did anything?!

767
00:46:12,503 --> 00:46:14,338
You don't think we all put
on our smiley faces for you

768
00:46:14,371 --> 00:46:16,006
when you stopped by?!

769
00:46:16,039 --> 00:46:17,407
You should have told me.

770
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,443
Your parents weren't
gonna admit anything.

771
00:46:19,476 --> 00:46:21,912
The neighbors didn't
want to get involved.

772
00:46:21,945 --> 00:46:25,149
The abuse was bad
before you removed us.

773
00:46:25,182 --> 00:46:27,384
But it went to a whole other
level when they moved us to

774
00:46:27,417 --> 00:46:31,288
that house in the woods
where no one heard us

775
00:46:31,321 --> 00:46:34,458
and they did whatever
they wanted.

776
00:46:34,491 --> 00:46:38,262
I'm sorry.

777
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:46,303
We should have never
gone back to them.

778
00:46:49,206 --> 00:46:56,046
All of your studies and charts
and statistics removed us from a

779
00:46:56,079 --> 00:47:01,151
safe, stable home and sent us
back to the people that hurt us.

780
00:47:01,185 --> 00:47:05,055
I have spent my life
fighting to protect children.

781
00:47:05,088 --> 00:47:08,292
I am on the front
lines everyday.

782
00:47:08,325 --> 00:47:12,329
Don't you think the
red tape frustrates me?

783
00:47:12,362 --> 00:47:13,630
Not only do I have
to fight the parents,

784
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:17,301
but I have to fight the system.

785
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:25,342
I have something
I wanna show you.

786
00:47:26,276 --> 00:47:34,284
[John gathers
papers and a knife]

787
00:47:37,621 --> 00:47:38,422
No!

788
00:47:38,455 --> 00:47:39,156
No!

789
00:47:39,189 --> 00:47:47,197
No!

790
00:47:47,631 --> 00:47:52,135
Here's the court order
removing us from our parents.

791
00:47:52,169 --> 00:47:56,473
And here's the court order
kicking us back to them.

792
00:47:56,506 --> 00:48:00,711
What one hand giveth,
the other hand taketh away.

793
00:48:00,744 --> 00:48:05,315
It breaks my heart
that we got it wrong.

794
00:48:05,349 --> 00:48:08,986
It was our hearts that were
broken because you got it wrong.

795
00:48:09,019 --> 00:48:10,954
What about my boys?

796
00:48:10,988 --> 00:48:14,157
Your boys will feel the same
pain that was inflicted on us.

797
00:48:14,191 --> 00:48:16,159
Not me.

798
00:48:16,193 --> 00:48:19,396
Your parents.

799
00:48:19,429 --> 00:48:22,266
Is this your goal here?

800
00:48:22,299 --> 00:48:23,500
To destroy as many lives
as you can because

801
00:48:23,533 --> 00:48:27,971
you had a shitty childhood?

802
00:48:28,005 --> 00:48:28,972
Well guess what?

803
00:48:29,006 --> 00:48:33,110
You're not the only ones.

804
00:48:33,143 --> 00:48:39,483
My boys have not had a
walk in the park either.

805
00:48:39,516 --> 00:48:43,353
Their father is a
violent alcoholic.

806
00:48:43,387 --> 00:48:48,425
I tried to fix him
because that's who I am.

807
00:48:48,458 --> 00:48:54,598
It took me years, years
to realize that I couldn't.

808
00:48:54,631 --> 00:48:58,669
And then finally I
took the boys and I left.

809
00:48:58,702 --> 00:49:02,773
If something happens to me,
my ex-husband will raise them.

810
00:49:02,806 --> 00:49:06,076
You realize that, right?

811
00:49:06,109 --> 00:49:07,611
How do you think
they're gonna affect society

812
00:49:07,644 --> 00:49:12,115
with that kind of upbringing?

813
00:49:12,149 --> 00:49:15,786
I'm their Helen Decker.

814
00:49:15,819 --> 00:49:20,791
Whatever happens to me
in this room right now

815
00:49:20,824 --> 00:49:25,262
will hurt innocent people
for years to come.

816
00:49:25,295 --> 00:49:29,099
[woman sobs]

817
00:49:29,132 --> 00:49:32,669
John?

818
00:49:32,703 --> 00:49:35,205
Turn it off.

819
00:49:35,238 --> 00:49:37,274
[sobbing]

820
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:40,577
[glitching sound]

821
00:49:40,610 --> 00:49:44,381
We can't just leave her here!

822
00:49:44,414 --> 00:49:48,385
That's exactly
what we're gonna do.

823
00:49:48,418 --> 00:49:50,654
[footsteps]

824
00:49:50,687 --> 00:49:52,422
Wait a minute.

825
00:49:52,456 --> 00:49:54,091
This is my life, too.

826
